Bidvest, Sun International May Move: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-08-29T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/bidvest-sun-international-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close. The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose
75.60, or 0.3 percent, to 29,425.05 by the 5 p.m. close in
Johannesburg.  Bidvest Group Ltd. (BVT)  : The industrial holding company
reports earnings for the year through June. The stock was little
changed at 143.49 rand.  DRDGold Ltd. (DRD)  : The gold producer reports earnings
for the year through June. The stock fell 4 cents, or 1.1
percent, to 3.61 rand.  Sun International Ltd. (SUI SJ): The hotel and leisure
company reports earnings for the year through June. The stock
declined 18 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 86.82 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
